My name is Melinda Gordon.

3
00:00:12,201 --> 00:00:14,787
I'm married,
I live in a small town,

4
00:00:15,930 --> 00:00:17,644
and I own
an antique shop.

5
00:00:17,668 --> 00:00:19,632
I might be just like you.

6
00:00:19,662 --> 00:00:24,050
Except that from the time I was a little
girl, I knew that I could talk to the dead.

7
00:00:25,017 --> 00:00:28,007
Earthbound spirits,
my grandmother called them.

8
00:00:28,636 --> 00:00:31,108
They're stuck here because they have
unfinished business with the living

9
00:00:31,143 --> 00:00:33,516
and they come to me
for help.

10
00:00:36,449 --> 00:00:41,687
In order to tell you my
story, I have to tell you theirs.

11
00:00:43,354 --> 00:00:45,259
<i>Previously
on ghost whisperer...</i>

12
00:00:45,259 --> 00:00:47,655
there's a plane in the air...

13
00:00:47,677 --> 00:00:49,954
no one is flying it!

14
00:00:53,915 --> 00:00:57,232
Yeah, I really don't get the feeling
that he was on that flight.

15
00:00:57,237 --> 00:00:57,981
I mean, what are the chances?

16
00:00:58,014 --> 00:00:59,961
I can't lose
my brother, melinda.

17
00:01:01,315 --> 00:01:04,381
- Wait!
- They're mine.

18
00:01:12,114 --> 00:01:15,847
I've been trying to work up
the courage to go in there,

19
00:01:16,563 --> 00:01:18,997
- look at the passenger list.
- Andrea...

20
00:01:19,011 --> 00:01:21,016
there's
something I have to tell you.

21
00:01:21,050 --> 00:01:23,045
- You saw mitch.
- Andrea--

22
00:01:23,051 --> 00:01:26,807
- Don't! No. No.
- But I'm not sure--

23
00:01:26,808 --> 00:01:28,805
no way.
It's not him.

24
00:01:28,821 --> 00:01:30,914
It was 250 people, jim.

25
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:33,176
Do I really have
the right to ignore that?

26
00:01:33,179 --> 00:01:36,453
What about the thousands people
you could help the rest of your life?

27
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:39,105
You can't trick those souls
into staying here.

28
00:01:39,107 --> 00:01:43,191
I will release
all your precious souls.

29
00:01:43,227 --> 00:01:46,960
And in return,
I'll take...you.

30
00:01:47,374 --> 00:01:49,660
Mitch!

31
00:01:54,995 --> 00:01:58,411
- Mitch?
- I'm so sorry, Mitch.

32
00:01:58,413 --> 00:02:00,549
I was supposed
to be on that plane, Melinda,

33
00:02:00,555 --> 00:02:02,547
I can't believe Andrea
it's dead.

34
00:02:03,054 --> 00:02:04,347
How'd it happen?

35
00:02:04,353 --> 00:02:08,126
She was driving
to your apartment in the city.

36
00:02:08,903 --> 00:02:11,316
She tried so hard
to reach you.

37
00:02:11,812 --> 00:02:14,905
I guess her car got caught in the
path of the plane.

38
00:02:14,909 --> 00:02:18,377
- Do you think she suffered?
- No.

39
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:23,963
No, I don't think so.

40
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,313
This can't be happening!

41
00:02:30,179 --> 00:02:33,232
she's mine!

42
00:02:56,262 --> 00:03:01,326
- Andrea! Andrea!
- Melinda, I don't know what's happening!

43
00:03:01,330 --> 00:03:03,655
- Please, help me!
- I've been looking for you, where are you?

44
00:03:03,699 --> 00:03:05,806
At the store.
I'm so scared!

45
00:03:05,810 --> 00:03:08,735
- Well, can you get to my house?
- I don't know!

46
00:03:08,741 --> 00:03:13,204
Ok. I'll come to you.
I have really good news.

47
00:03:13,227 --> 00:03:15,302
Hello?!

48
00:03:15,307 --> 00:03:17,274
How is she calling you?

49
00:03:17,429 --> 00:03:20,891
She had her cell phone with her. You know,
maybe she can tap into the energy fields.

50
00:03:21,055 --> 00:03:23,650
- I'll come with you?
- No, she's gonna want to talk to me alone.

51
00:03:23,696 --> 00:03:27,582
She's gonna be so happy!

52
00:03:45,922 --> 00:03:48,155
Don't!

53
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,076
The light hurts my eyes.

54
00:03:53,252 --> 00:03:56,156
Andrea, I've been
so worried about you!

55
00:03:56,161 --> 00:03:59,754
- Tell me everything's gonna be ok.
- I think maybe it is.

56
00:03:59,759 --> 00:04:02,314
You may not really be dead.

57
00:04:02,467 --> 00:04:04,464
- What?
- It's truim found you,

58
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:06,415
Jim found you,
your body.

59
00:04:06,418 --> 00:04:09,693
You're in a coma at mercy hospital,
but you're gonna be ok.

60
00:04:09,728 --> 00:04:13,534
You're just out of body until ypu come out
of the coma. Doctors are working so hard.

61
00:04:13,626 --> 00:04:17,133
You're not lying to me? You're not just
trying to make me feel better?

62
00:04:17,154 --> 00:04:20,152
Look, you're not out of the woods.
You have some injuries.

63
00:04:20,157 --> 00:04:22,429
but the doctors think that
you're gonna pull through.

64
00:04:22,994 --> 00:04:26,281
We've been with you
at that hospital every day.

65
00:04:26,385 --> 00:04:30,389
- It's scary here.
- What's it like?

66
00:04:30,404 --> 00:04:34,419
I don't really like to look around too
much. There...there are people here.

67
00:04:34,421 --> 00:04:36,677
- People?
- Not people...

68
00:04:37,051 --> 00:04:42,306
I guess, maybe, um, beings or something?
They're dark, and they're always watching.

69
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:50,673
- I can't really see.
- Melinda!

70
00:04:51,008 --> 00:04:53,314
Melinda... Open the door!

71
00:04:53,318 --> 00:04:56,872
- Open the door, let me in!
- I can't!

72
00:04:56,888 --> 00:04:59,204
- The door!
- It won't open!

73
00:05:00,537 --> 00:05:03,512
Andrea!...
No... No!

74
00:05:03,516 --> 00:05:06,311
- No!
- It's ok, it's ok.

75
00:05:06,316 --> 00:05:08,830
- Shh, just a dream.
- Sorry.

76
00:05:09,674 --> 00:05:11,759
Want some water?

77
00:05:12,415 --> 00:05:14,448
I dreamt
that she was alive,

78
00:05:14,976 --> 00:05:18,519
that you found her body
and that she was gonna be ok.

79
00:05:18,894 --> 00:05:21,598
Think she's trying
to come to you in the dreams?

80
00:05:21,603 --> 00:05:25,087
It doesn't usually work that way.
Scared the hell out of me, though.

81
00:05:25,163 --> 00:05:26,566
No kidding.

82
00:05:26,770 --> 00:05:29,438
- Sorry I woke you.
- Yeah, me, too.

83
00:05:29,443 --> 00:05:33,937
I was dreaming that I was floating on
a river of beer and I had a big cup.

84
00:05:34,030 --> 00:05:36,487
Are your dreams
always that complex?

85
00:05:36,501 --> 00:05:38,644
Pretty much.

86
00:05:39,448 --> 00:05:40,676
Gonna be able to sleep?

87
00:05:40,747 --> 00:05:45,524
I don't want to keep you up. You know what,
I think I'm just gonna go downstairs and read.

88
00:05:57,564 --> 00:05:59,561
Romano.

89
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:02,035
Mine.

90
00:06:05,243 --> 00:06:08,689
Help me.

91
00:06:47,078 --> 00:06:50,691
Death is nothing at all.
It does not count.

92
00:06:50,941 --> 00:06:53,944
I have only slipped away
into the next room.

93
00:06:53,990 --> 00:06:56,485
Everything remains
as it was.

94
00:06:56,763 --> 00:07:00,139
The old life that we live so fondly
together in unchanged.

95
00:07:00,146 --> 00:07:02,269
Is andrea here?

96
00:07:02,278 --> 00:07:06,702
Whatever we were
to each other, that we are still.

97
00:07:07,971 --> 00:07:12,995
- I am but waiting for you. For an inverval,
interval, somewhere very near... - No.

98
00:07:13,002 --> 00:07:17,608
I just don't understand why
she's not coming to me.

99
00:07:17,614 --> 00:07:20,000
- Maybe she's crossed over.
- No, she hasn'T.

100
00:07:20,007 --> 00:07:22,163
I would know if she did.

101
00:07:22,170 --> 00:07:24,442
I just can't figure out
what's keeping her here.

102
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:29,753
...How we shall laugh at the trouble
of parting when we meet again.

103
00:07:29,764 --> 00:07:33,759
Maybe she's still in the department.
I will be going to see later

104
00:07:50,206 --> 00:07:52,260
Thanks for everything
you did, melinda.

105
00:07:53,246 --> 00:07:57,592
I hope you know
how much andrea loved you.

106
00:07:57,599 --> 00:08:00,333
I loved her, too. So much.

107
00:08:01,361 --> 00:08:03,775
You were like her sister.

108
00:08:05,484 --> 00:08:08,751
Do you ever...feel like
she's with you??

109
00:08:08,755 --> 00:08:11,601
In some ways, you know,
like she's near you?

110
00:08:11,606 --> 00:08:13,972
No. Not really.

111
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:17,154
Do you?

112
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:20,127
I'd like to.

113
00:08:20,134 --> 00:08:24,938
Andrea said that you understood death
in ways that most people don'T.

114
00:08:25,777 --> 00:08:27,772
What else
did she say?

115
00:08:27,777 --> 00:08:32,311
Just that you knew
how to help people who were grieving.

116
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:35,635
Now I'm one of them.

117
00:08:38,114 --> 00:08:40,238
We both lost a sister.

118
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:48,814
Here in the stricken
town of grandview,

119
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:51,085
residents struggle to resume
their normal lives

120
00:08:51,090 --> 00:08:54,048
after the tragedy
of flight 395.

121
00:08:54,052 --> 00:08:56,318
We're here today to see
how they're doing. Excuse me,

122
00:08:56,324 --> 00:08:59,759
We're here in grandview today to see
what kind of progress the town is making

123
00:08:59,766 --> 00:09:01,551
in the aftermath
of the plane crash.

124
00:09:01,587 --> 00:09:03,802
How do you think
things are going?

125
00:09:04,641 --> 00:09:07,694
Um...I can only say that the people
in this town are really strong,

126
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:09,626
they're survivors.

127
00:09:09,672 --> 00:09:12,118
- We're gonna be ok.
- Thank you.

128
00:09:12,974 --> 00:09:14,978
Well, there you have it
from a local merchant.

129
00:09:14,985 --> 00:09:18,891
This town is grieving, but determined
to get back to business as usual.

130
00:09:30,504 --> 00:09:33,599
Andrea?...
Are you here?

131
00:09:36,477 --> 00:09:39,234
I just want
to talk to you, please.

132
00:09:39,239 --> 00:09:41,865
I know that you're scared.

133
00:10:36,826 --> 00:10:40,029
- Where's andrea?
- I'll be glad to take a message.

134
00:10:40,036 --> 00:10:43,812
- What are you doing to her?
- I don't have to do anything.

135
00:10:43,819 --> 00:10:46,895
- She's doing it all to herself.
- Who are you?

136
00:10:46,902 --> 00:10:49,905
I was alive once.
Just like you.

137
00:10:49,911 --> 00:10:53,945
- ...I had names, I had lis.
- Romano... Is that your name?

138
00:10:53,953 --> 00:10:56,129
- I'm just a humble teacher.
- Teacher?

139
00:10:56,134 --> 00:10:58,721
Trying to spread the word.

140
00:10:58,727 --> 00:11:02,214
- Much like yourself.
- What are you doing here? What do you want?

141
00:11:02,221 --> 00:11:04,505
- I have what I want.
- No. No, you don'T.

142
00:11:04,512 --> 00:11:08,885
Andrea will not go with you. I
know her. She's going into the light.

143
00:11:08,954 --> 00:11:12,379
I'm going to have her,
and I'm going to have you, too.

144
00:11:12,381 --> 00:11:14,398
It's just a matter of time.

145
00:12:18,945 --> 00:12:21,991
Andrea, you have to cross
over. Please let me help you.

146
00:12:21,996 --> 00:12:25,953
- I can'T. - Why not?
- You could never understand why!

